墨西拿鹽度危機的起因有多種說法，但普遍共識是古氣候變化和地質構造運動是主要原因<ref name ="Gargani-2007">{{cite journal |vauthors=Gargani J, Rigollet C |year=2007|title=Mediterranean Sea level variations during the Messinian Salinity Crisis.|journal=Geophysical Research Letters |volume=34 |issue= L10405 |pages= L10405|doi=10.1029/2007GL029885|bibcode=2007GeoRL..3410405G|s2cid=128771539|url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/8b87f296fc8153f8346509279b9423a857a571de|doi-access=free }}</ref>，而兩者的影響規模大小仍有爭議和不同解釋<ref name="Van dijk-etal-1998">van Dijk, J.P., Barberis, A., Cantarella, G., and Massa, E. (1998); Central Mediterranean Messinian basin evolution. Tectono-eustasy or eustato-tectonics? Annales Tectonicae, 12, n. 1-2, 7-27.</ref><ref name=”Gargani“>Gargani J, Rigollet C (2007). "Mediterranean Sea level variations during the Messinian Salinity Crisis". Geophysical Research Letters. 34 (L10405): L10405. Bibcode:2007GeoRL..3410405G</ref><ref name=”Dijk“>van Dijk, J.P., Barberis, A., Cantarella, G., and Massa, E. (1998); Central Mediterranean Messinian basin evolution. Tectono-eustasy or eustato-tectonics? Annales Tectonicae, 12, n. 1-2, 7-27</ref>。亞歐板塊和非洲板塊之間的弧型構造帶直布羅陀弧被認為是導致地中海與大西洋分離的原因<ref name="Weijermars“">Weijermars, Ruud (May 1988). "Neogene tectonics in the Western Mediterranean may have caused the Messinian salinity crisis and an associated glacial event". Tectonophysics. 148 (3–4): 211–219</ref><ref name=”Dijk1“>van Dijk J.P., Okkes F.W.M. (1991). "Neogene tectonostratigraphy and kinematics of Calabrian Basins. implications for the geodynamics of the Central Mediterranean". Tectonophysics. 196 (1–2): 23–60</ref>，該地區的板塊運動控制了中新世晚期直布羅陀海峽的開啓和關閉，至於這一構造運動的細節仍然有不同說法<ref name=”Lonergan“>Lonergan, Lidia; White, Nicky (June 1997). "Origin of the Betic-Rif mountain belt". Tectonics. 16 (3): 504–522</ref><ref name=”Platt“> Platt, J. P.; Vissers, R.L.M. (1989). "Extensional collapse of thickened continental lithosphere: A working hypothesis for the Alboran Sea and Gibraltar arc". Geology. 17 (6): 540</ref><ref name=”Jackson“>Jackson, J.A.; Austrheim, H.; McKenzie, D.; Priestley, K. (2004). "Metastability, mechanical strength, and the support of mountain belts". Geology. 32 (7): 625</ref>，有三種地球動力學模型可能適合相關數據<ref name="van Dijk-and-Okkes_1991">{{cite journal | author = van Dijk J.P., Okkes F.W.M. | year = 1991 | title = Neogene tectonostratigraphy and kinematics of Calabrian Basins. implications for the geodynamics of the Central Mediterranean | journal = Tectonophysics | volume = 196 | issue = 1–2| pages = 23–60 | doi=10.1016/0040-1951(91)90288-4| bibcode = 1991Tectp.196...23V}}</ref>，移動的俯衝帶可能導致了週期性的區域隆起，火山岩的變化表明特提斯海邊緣的俯衝帶可能向西捲縮，從而改變了西地中海下方岩漿的化學成分和密度<ref name=Lonergan1997>{{cite journal|last1=Lonergan|first1=Lidia|last2=White|first2=Nicky|title=Origin of the Betic-Rif mountain belt|journal=Tectonics|date=June 1997|volume=16|issue=3|pages=504–522|doi=10.1029/96TC03937|bibcode=1997Tecto..16..504L|hdl=10044/1/21686|hdl-access=free}}</ref>。除了構造運動外，古氣候變化而導致的全球海面升降是另外一個重要因素，在地中海海域的鑽探發現蒸發岩層中常有[[遠海沉積物|遠海沉積物]]夾層，内含常規海洋相生物，無過渡帶，代表陸表鹽湖環境與常規海洋環境存在周期性快速互變，這種周期性顯然與全球海平面的升降有關<ref name=”Sonnenfeld “>Sonnenfeld, Peter,. 2015.The Significance of Upper Miocene (Messinian) Evaporites in the Mediterranean Sea. The Journal of Geology. Vol. 83, No. 3  P. 287-311</ref>。

==過程==
[[File:MSC basin hypotheses.svg|thumb|350px|墨西拿鹽度危機期間蒸發岩形成的假設
<br />a: 歷時沉積：蒸發岩（粉紅色）首先沉積在陸上盆地，隨著地中海（深藍色）的範圍向門戶減小，更靠近大西洋。 淺藍色顯示原始海平面。
<br />b: 邊緣盆地同步沉積： 海平面略有下降，但整個盆地仍與大西洋相連。 減少的流入量只允許蒸發岩在淺盆地中積累。
<br />c: 同步、全盆地沉積。 構造活動（深灰色）對大西洋海道的關閉或限制導致整個盆地同時蒸發岩沉積； 水池可能不需要完全排空，因為鹽分會通過蒸發濃縮。]]
地中海深海海底的沉積物樣本，包括蒸發岩礦物、土壤和植物化石，表明[[直布羅陀海峽|直布羅陀海峽]]的前身在大約596萬年前閉合，將地中海與大西洋隔開<ref>{{Cite book|last=Cunliffe|first=Sir Barry|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H583DwAAQBAJ&newbks=0&printsec=frontcover&pg=PT56&dq&hl=en|title=On the Ocean: The Mediterranean and the Atlantic from prehistory to AD 1500|date=2017-09-29|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-107534-6|pages=56|language=en|quote=the remnant Tethys became joined to the Atlantic, roughly along the line of what was to become the Strait of Gibraltar. About 5.96 million years ago this gap closed, initiating what is known as the Messinian Salinity Crisis, which lasted for more than half a million years before the Atlantic was reunited once more with the Mediterranean.|access-date=2021-10-04|archive-date=2021-10-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211012234216/https://books.google.com/books?id=H583DwAAQBAJ&newbks=0&printsec=frontcover&pg=PT56&dq&hl=en|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Gargani J., Rigollet C. 2007 L10405">{{cite journal|author1=Gargani J. |author2=Rigollet C. |title=Mediterranean Sea level variations during the Messinian Salinity Crisis.|journal=Geophysical Research Letters|date=2007|volume=34|issue=10 |page= L10405|doi=10.1029/2007gl029885|bibcode=2007GeoRL..3410405G|s2cid=128771539 |url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/8b87f296fc8153f8346509279b9423a857a571de |doi-access=free}}</ref>。該地區普遍乾燥的氣候在1000年內使地中海盆地幾乎完全乾涸，留下了一個低於正常海平面達3至5公里（1.9至3.1英里）的乾涸盆地，其中有幾個類似於今天[[死海|死海]]的高鹽區。在550萬年前左右，乾燥的氣候條件减緩，導致盆地從河流接收更多淡水，逐漸將高鹽湖填充並稀釋成更大的鹹水區（與今天的[[裏海|裏海]]很相似），在[[墨西拿期|墨西拿期]]末，地中海盆内所含鹽分完全沉積到盆地中心，地中海周邊陸上及海底留下了大量侵蝕不整合面<ref name="Schreiber“">Schreiber, C. S., et al. 1976. Depositional environments of Upper Miocene (Messinian) evaporite deposits of the Sicilian Basin. Sedimentology, Vol. 23 Issue 6. p.729-760</ref><ref name=”Lofi”>Lofi, Johanna, et al. 2011. Seismic Atlas of the Messinian Salinity Crisis markers in the Mediterranean and Black Seas. Commission for the Geological Map of the World & Memories of the French Geological Society ISBN 2-85363-097-8</ref>，例如在意大利西岸薩迪納島及西班牙東岸、西西里盆地、塞浦路斯、敘利亞及黎巴嫩外海等地<ref name=”Maillard”> Mailland, Agnes, et al., 2020. New onshore/offshore evidence of the Messinian Erosion Surface from key areas: The Ibiza-Balearic Promontory and the Orosei-Eastern Sardinian margin.Bulletin de la Société Géologique de France。 Vol。191。https://doi.org/10.1051/bsgf/2020007</ref><ref name=“Schreiber “>Schreiber, C. S., et al. 1976. Depositional environments of Upper Miocene (Messinian) evaporite deposits of the Sicilian Basin. Sedimentology, Vol. 23 Issue 6. p.729-760,</ref><ref name=”Madof”>Madof, A. S., etal., 2019. Discovery of vast fluvial deposits provides evidence for drawdown during the late Miocene Messinian salinity crisis. Geology Vol. 47, P. 171–174</ref>。533萬年前，直布羅陀海峽終於重新開放，墨西拿鹽度危機就此結束，當時大西洋的海水迅速填滿了地中海盆地，稱之為[[贊克爾期洪水|贊克爾期洪水]]<ref name="ReferenceA">{{cite journal|last1=Clauzon|first1=Georges|last2=Suc|first2=Jean-Pierre|last3=Gautier|first3=François|last4=Berger|first4=André|last5=Loutre|first5=Marie-France|title=Alternate interpretation of the Messinian salinity crisis: Controversy resolved?|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_geology_1996-04_24_4/page/363|journal=Geology|date=1996|volume=24|issue=4|pages=363|doi=10.1130/0091-7613(1996)024<0363:AIOTMS>2.3.CO;2|bibcode=1996Geo....24..363C}}</ref>。

==影響==
[[File:Gypsum_cones.jpg|thumb]]
來自地中海的水將在世界海洋中重新分配，使全球海平面上升10米（33英尺）。地中海盆地也在其海底封存了相當一部分來自地球海洋的鹽，使世界海洋的平均鹽度降低了6-10%<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.geo.arizona.edu/geo2xx/geo212.034/Lect17.html Lecture 17: Mediterranean<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100523081426/http://www.geo.arizona.edu/geo2xx/geo212.034/Lect17.html |date=2010-05-23 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last = Warren | first = John K. | title = Evaporites: sediments, resources and hydrocarbons | page = 147 | publisher = Birkhäuser | year = 2006 | isbn = 978-3-540-26011-0 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=0x7Q2elh-joC&pg=PA47 | access-date = 2016-12-15 | archive-date = 2021-10-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211004080836/https://books.google.com/books?id=0x7Q2elh-joC&pg=PA47 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。隨著地中海水域鹽度的迅速增高，大量無法忍受高鹽度的海洋生物滅絕。盆地的低海拔將通過絕熱加熱使其在夏季變得非常熱，硬石膏的存在支持了這一結論，硬石膏僅沉積在溫度高於35°C（95°F）的水中。流入盆地的河流會將河床切割得更深，[[尼羅河|尼羅河]]至少在地中海盆地邊緣切割了2400米深的下切谷。有一種觀點認為，在墨西拿期[[紅海|紅海]]在蘇伊士與地中海相連，但沒有與[[印度洋|印度洋]]相連，並隨著地中海乾涸<ref>{{cite web| title = Vast "Grand Canyon" Lurks 8,200 Feet BENEATH Cairo, Egypt | publisher = Biot Report 403 | date = September 21, 2006 | url = https://groups.yahoo.com/group/InPursuitofWisdom/message/3821
}}</ref><ref>https://agupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1029/2007GL032494 {{Wayback|url=https://agupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1029/2007GL032494 |date=20170630033829 }}, ''[[Geophysical_Research_Letters|Geophysical Research Letters]]'', ''Evaporite accumulation during the Messinian Salinity Crisis: The Suez Rift case'', by Julien Gargani, Isabelle Moretti, Jean Letouzey, First published: 16 January 2008, https://doi.org/10.1029/2007GL032494</ref>。墨西拿鹽度危機還為許多非洲物種，包括[[羚羊|羚羊]]、[[大象|大象]]和[[河馬|河馬]]，提供了一個機會，當海平面下降時，它們可以遷移到靠近下降的大河的空盆地，到達馬爾他等內陸潮濕凉爽的高地，海水回流後，它們留在群島上，在更新世期間，它們在島上經歷了[[島嶼矮化|島嶼矮化]]，由此產生了克里特島河馬、塞浦路斯矮河馬等已滅絕物種，其中賽普勒斯矮河馬一直存活到[[更新世|更新世]]末或[[全新世|全新世]]早期<ref>{{Cite journal | author = A. Simmons | year = 2000 | title = Faunal extinction in an island society: pygmy hippopotamus hunters of Cyprus | journal = [[Geoarchaeology|Geoarchaeology]] | volume = 15 | issue = 4 | pages = 379–381 | doi = 10.1002/(SICI)1520-6548(200004)15:4<379::AID-GEA7>3.0.CO;2-E}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author1=Gargani J. |author2=Rigollet C |author3=Scarselli S. | title = Isostatic response and geomorphological evolution of the Nile valley during the Messinian salinity crisis.| journal = Bull. Soc. Géol. Fr. | volume = 181| pages = 19–26| doi=10.2113/gssgfbull.181.1.19|year=2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal| author = Gargani J.| title = Modelling of the erosion in the Rhone valley during the Messinian crisis (France)| journal =  Quaternary International| volume = 121| pages = 13–22| doi=10.1016/j.quaint.2004.01.020| bibcode =2004QuInt.121...13G| year = 2004}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Petronio |first=C. |year=1995 |title=Note on the taxonomy of Pleistocene hippopotamuses |journal=Ibex |volume=3 |pages=53–55 |url=http://www.mountainecology.org/IBEX3/pdf/Art_Capitolo1/note_taxonomy_pleistocene.pdf |access-date=2008-08-23 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080912012236/http://www.mountainecology.org/IBEX3/pdf/Art_Capitolo1/note_taxonomy_pleistocene.pdf |archive-date=2008-09-12 }}</ref>。

==遺跡==
[[File:Yesares_gypsum.jpg|thumb]]
地中海水位下降的主要證據來自許多現在被淹沒的峽谷的遺跡，這些地中海盆地兩側的峽谷被流入原為海底的平原的河流切割<ref name="Gargani J., Rigollet C, Scarselli S. 2010 19–26">{{cite journal|author1=Gargani J. |author2=Rigollet C |author3=Scarselli S. | date = 2010| title = Isostatic response and geomorphological evolution of the Nile valley during the Messinian salinity crisis.| journal = Bull. Soc. Géol. Fr. | volume = 181| pages = 19–26| doi=10.2113/gssgfbull.181.1.19
}}</ref><ref name="Gargani J. 2004 13–22">{{cite journal| author = Gargani J.| date = 2004| title = Modelling of the erosion in the Rhone valley during the Messinian crisis (France)| journal =  Quaternary International| volume = 121| issue = 1| pages = 13–22| doi=10.1016/j.quaint.2004.01.020| bibcode = 2004QuInt.121...13G
 }}</ref>。[[尼羅河|尼羅河]]在[[阿斯旺|阿斯旺]]將河床切割到海平面以下幾百英尺，1967年伊萬·S·丘馬科夫在那裡發現了上新世的海洋[[有孔蟲|有孔蟲]]<ref>{{cite book|last=Warren|first=J.K.|title=Evaporites: sediments, resources and hydrocarbons|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ihny39BvVhIC&pg=PA352|year=2006|publisher=Birkhäuser|isbn=978-3-540-26011-0|page=352|access-date=2016-12-15|archive-date=2021-11-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211106024429/https://books.google.com/books?id=ihny39BvVhIC&pg=PA352|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在以色列的阿非[[海底峽谷|海底峽谷]]（Afig submarine canyon），峽谷充填物下層是石膏、上層是河流相沉積物，代表在[[中新世|中新世]]晚期海底曾露于陸表被河流切割。根據峽谷深度，海水面曾下降800公尺<ref name=”Druckman “>Druckman, Y., et al ., 1995.The buried Afiq Canyon (Eastern Mediterranean, Israel): a case study of a Tertiary submarine canyon exposed in Late Messinian times. Marine Geology Volume 123, Issues 3–4, April 1995, Pages 167-185)</ref>。在利比亞北部有一條[[中新世|中新世]]晚期的[[下切谷|下切谷]]，長150公里，至少700公尺深，被河流切割的是[[中新世|中新世]]中期[[石灰岩|石灰岩]]，下切谷中的冲填物是[[上新世|上新世]]河流沉積物。同樣年代的下切谷也分佈於利比亞東部及埃及西部，這代表地中海的海面在[[中新世|中新世]]晚期至少下降700公尺<ref name=”Barr”> Barr, F. T.  and Walker, B. R. 2004. LATE TERTIARY CHANNEL SYSTEM IN NORTHERN LIBYA AND ITS IMPLICATIONS ON MEDITERRANEAN SEA LEVEL CHANGES. in Petroleum Geology of Libya, ed. Hallett, Don.  Publ. Elservier. ISBN 50525-3</ref>。在敘利亞及黎巴嫩外海，埋藏在海底深部的晚[[中新世|中新世]]晚期的蒸發岩上部也有大面積的河流相沉積物，這代表地中海在晚中新世幾乎乾枯的環境<ref name=”Madof”>Madof, A. S., etal., 2019. Discovery of vast fluvial deposits provides evidence for drawdown during the late Miocene Messinian salinity crisis. Geology Vol. 47, P. 171–174</ref>。在地中海的許多地方，人們發現了泥質沉積物在陽光和乾旱下乾燥開裂的化石裂縫<ref name="Wade">{{cite journal|last=Wade|first=B.S.|author2=Brown P.R.|year=2006|title=Calcareous nannofossils in extreme environments: The Messinian Salinity Crisis, Polemi Basin, Cyprus|journal=Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology|volume=233|issue=3–4|pages=271–286|doi=10.1016/j.palaeo.2005.10.007|url=http://geotest.tamu.edu/userfiles/42/wade2006.pdf|access-date=2016-12-15|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303181710/http://geotest.tamu.edu/userfiles/42/wade2006.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

